params.name: data.name
params.description: The resource name of the phrase matcher. Format: projects/{project}/locations/{location}/phraseMatchers/{phrase_matcher}

params.name: data.revision_id
params.description: Output only. Immutable. The revision ID of the phrase matcher. A new revision is committed whenever the matcher is changed, except when it is activated or deactivated. A server generated random ID will be used. Example: locations/global/phraseMatchers/my-first-matcher@1234567

params.name: data.version_tag
params.description: The customized version tag to use for the phrase matcher. If not specified, it will default to revision_id.

params.name: data.revision_create_time
params.description: Output only. The timestamp of when the revision was created. It is also the create time when a new matcher is added.

params.name: data.display_name
params.description: The human-readable name of the phrase matcher.

params.name: data.type
params.description: Required. The type of this phrase matcher.

params.name: data.active
params.description: Applies the phrase matcher only when it is active.

params.name: data.phrase_match_rule_groups
params.description: A list of phase match rule groups that are included in this matcher.

params.name: data.activation_update_time
params.description: Output only. The most recent time at which the activation status was updated.

params.name: data.role_match
params.description: The role whose utterances the phrase matcher should be matched against. If the role is ROLE_UNSPECIFIED it will be matched against any utterances in the transcript.

params.name: data.update_time
params.description: Output only. The most recent time at which the phrase matcher was updated.
